<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Fourth session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Algeria (on behalf of the Group of Arab States), Pakistan (on behalf of 
the Organization of the Islamic Conference):  draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b>4/&#8230;  Human rights situation in the Occupied Palestinian Territory 
</b></p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i> Recalling</i> that the mandate of the Special Rapporteur on the situation of human rights in 
the Palestinian territories occupied since 1967 appointed in compliance with Commission on 
Human Rights resolution 1993/2 of 19 February 1993 has been established until the end of the 
Israeli occupation, 
</p>
<p><i> Gravely concerned</i> that the Palestinian people continue to suffer from the Israeli 
occupation and its gross violations of human rights, 
</p>
<p><i> Decides</i> that the mandate of the Special Rapporteur is until the end of the Israeli 
occupation. 
</p>
